    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.51/567</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">External Debt of Honduras</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It is understood that the pending Agreement for the settlement of this debt,
                    which was approved by the Council of Foreign Bondholders in May 1923, and which
                    still requires ratification by the Congress of Honduras, is shortly to be
                    submitted to the latter body.</p>
                <p>As it is believed that the United States Government in 1923 favoured a solution
                    of this question on the terms stated in the pending Agreement<note n="36"
                        xml:id="d301fn36">See footnote 35, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> it is hoped that the United States representative at Tegucigalpa may
                    receive instructions to support His Majesty’s Consul there in urging the
                    submission of the Agreement to the Congress of Honduras for ratification, in
                    order that this long outstanding question may be disposed of as soon as
                    possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-03-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 12, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
